snippet.textDisplay:
please remember that, due to where the majority of your audience came from, they are young. You speak often about weight, the scale, restricting food, dieting, binging at night, etc...
For most, we understand that this is life and it is normal to struggle/fluctuate/motivate ourselves... but some of your young audience is really searching to find a thread of self confidence and positive body image. Fixating on your weight may not be the best thing to focus on going forwards. Maybe mention exercise and eating healthy as this is INSANELY important for health, but leave out the talk about food restriction and weighing yourself as it may be difficult for the young ones to understand the healthy balance. Self love/acceptance is number one!!

Thanks for all of your amazing content♥️

Ps- coming from an almost 30 year old who struggled with disordered eating from age 11-19
